tldr: The user requested a thorough aesthetic review and improvement of their
  sleep questionnaire app. I implemented a new sleep-themed color palette,
  redesigned the main layout and UI components, ensured consistent styling
  across all form sections, and polished the report section. I also fixed a
  console error related to null input values.
overview: The user wanted to transform the generic look of their sleep
  questionnaire app into a more beautiful and professional interface. I started
  by analyzing the existing design, identifying areas like the color palette,
  layout, and form elements that needed improvement. I then implemented a new
  calming, sleep-themed color palette, updated the main questionnaire form with
  decorative background elements and a redesigned progress indicator, and
  enhanced the welcome screen with feature cards and softer alerts. All 14 form
  sections were updated to use consistent card-style groupings and theme colors,
  moving away from plain gray boxes. Key UI components like checkboxes, radio
  buttons, and sliders were polished with improved visual feedback and hover
  states. Finally, the report section was refined with consistent gradient
  headers and theme-aligned content. During the process, I also debugged and
  fixed a console error related to null values being passed to input fields,
  ensuring a robust and visually appealing application.
